# PokePon GitHub Pages deploy workflow

The live site is **https://pokepon.org**, served from the **`hamiebrooklyn.github.io`** repository (local path is often `~/Documents/GitHub/hamiebrooklyn.github.io`).

## When this applies

After you change website files (HTML, `assets/*.js`, `assets/*.css`, pages under `collection/`, `duel/`, `trades/`, etc.) for a user-facing feature or bugfix:

1. **Commit** in `hamiebrooklyn.github.io` with a clear message (what changed and why).
2. **Push** to `origin/main` so GitHub Pages updates — do not leave site-only work only on disk.
3. **Bump cache-busters** on touched assets (e.g. `collection.js?v=N`, `style.css?v=N` in the HTML that loads them).

## Bot API vs site

- **Website repo** → UI, client JS, styles.
- **`Poke-Cards` bot repo** (`~/Developer/Poke-Cards` or workspace clone) → `/api/*` handlers; commit and push separately when API changes are part of the same feature.
- Pages deploy alone is **not** enough when the bot API changed.

## Restart background services (required for API changes)

The bot and tunnel usually run **in the background** on the Mac host. After pulling or editing bot code, **you must restart them yourself** — do not assume a code push reloads the running process.

From `~/Developer/Poke-Cards` (or the active bot clone):

```bash
# 1. Stop old bot (launchd, nohup, anything on :8080)
bash scripts/stop-bot.sh
sleep 2

# 2. Start bot in background (same pattern as production)
nohup bash scripts/run-bot.sh >> logs/bot.log 2>&1 &

# 3. Confirm API is up
curl -s http://localhost:8080/api/health
```

If **https://api.pokepon.org** still returns 502/Bad Gateway, restart the Cloudflare tunnel (forwards to localhost:8080):

```bash
pkill -f "cloudflared tunnel run pokepon-api" 2>/dev/null || true
sleep 1
nohup cloudflared tunnel run pokepon-api >> logs/cloudflared.log 2>&1 &
curl -s https://api.pokepon.org/api/health
```

Other long-running services (only if relevant to the change):

- **GitHub Actions self-hosted runner** — restart only when CI/runner config changed, not for normal bot API edits.
- See `docs/MAC-STARTUP.md` in the bot repo for full stack checks (`pgrep -lf poke_pon_bot`, `pgrep -lf cloudflared`).

Treat **restart + health check** as part of “done” for any task that touches `poke_pon_bot/`.

## Unless the user says otherwise

- Do **not** skip push because of the general “only commit when asked” rule — **shipping site work includes push** once the user is iterating on pokepon.org features.
- Do **not** commit secrets (`.env`, tokens).
- Do **not** force-push `main`.

## Quick check before closing the task

```bash
cd ~/Documents/GitHub/hamiebrooklyn.github.io
git status -sb
git push origin main   # if ahead of origin

# If bot API changed:
cd ~/Developer/Poke-Cards
bash scripts/stop-bot.sh && sleep 2 && nohup bash scripts/run-bot.sh >> logs/bot.log 2>&1 &
curl -s http://localhost:8080/api/health
```
